## Task
> Execute the plan: set up Storybook Compodoc with Signal Inputs and Outputs for the ngx-smart-components Angular library in an Nx monorepo. Steps: (1) install @compodoc/compodoc, (2-3) enable compodoc in storybook and build-storybook project.json targets, (4) add resolveJsonModule to storybook tsconfig, (5) wire compodoc JSON and enable autodocs in preview.ts, (6) add signal input/output with JSDoc to component, (7) update stories with label arg.

## Orientation Findings

1. `package.json`: `@storybook/angular` is `10.3.5`, `@compodoc/compodoc` is NOT a direct dep. It IS installed as a transitive dep at `1.2.1` (verified in node_modules). `@storybook/global` is installed as a transitive dep at `5.0.0`.
2. `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`: Both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets have `"compodoc": false` and no `compodocArgs`. Need to change both to `true` and add the args.
3. `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`: File exists but is empty (0 bytes / 1 line).
4. `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`: Has `"emitDecoratorMetadata": true` but no `resolveJsonModule`. Includes `../src/**/*.stories.ts` and `*.ts` globs.
5. `packages/ngx-smart-components/tsconfig.lib.json`: Exists, includes `src/**/*.ts`, excludes spec/test/stories files. Plan's `-p tsconfig.lib.json` assumption is verified.
6. `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.ts`: Component exists, no signal inputs/outputs yet.
7. `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`: `Primary` story has `args: {}`. `Heading` story play test checks for `NgxSmartComponents works!` -- after the template change to `{{ label() }} works!` with default `'NgxSmartComponents'`, rendered text will be `NgxSmartComponents works!`, so the Heading play assertion still passes without modification.

## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims

<pre_verified source="D:/projects/github/LayZeeDK/ngx-smart-components/node_modules/@compodoc/compodoc/package.json" claim_id="pv-1">
  <claim>@compodoc/compodoc 1.2.1 is installed as a transitive dependency; it does NOT need to be npm-installed from scratch, but adding it as a direct devDependency pins the version.</claim>
  <evidence method="Bash">
    "version": "1.2.1",
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="D:/projects/github/LayZeeDK/ngx-smart-components/node_modules/@storybook/global/package.json" claim_id="pv-2">
  <claim>@storybook/global 5.0.0 is available as a transitive dependency and can be imported in preview.ts without a separate npm install.</claim>
  <evidence method="Bash">
    "version": "5.0.0",
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="D:/projects/github/LayZeeDK/ngx-smart-components/packages/ngx-smart-components/tsconfig.lib.json" claim_id="pv-3">
  <claim>tsconfig.lib.json exists at the path used in compodocArgs (-p) and includes src/**/*.ts -- the correct source set for compodoc.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
    "exclude": ["src/**/*.spec.ts", "src/**/*.test.ts", "**/*.stories.ts", "**/*.stories.js"]
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="D:/projects/github/LayZeeDK/ngx-smart-components/package.json" claim_id="pv-version-anchor-1">
  <claim>Installed version of @storybook/angular is 10.3.5; the plan's Storybook 10.3.5 references are version-anchored correctly.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    "@storybook/angular": "10.3.5",
    "storybook": "10.3.5",
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

## Source Material

--- Prior Strategic Direction (consultation 1) ---
1. Install `@compodoc/compodoc` as devDependency; the `@storybook/angular:start-storybook` executor's `compodoc: true` runs it automatically -- no manual addon wiring needed. The executor injects `__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` itself.
2. In `project.json`, set `compodoc: true` and add `"compodocArgs": ["-e", "json", "-d", "packages/ngx-smart-components", "-p", "packages/ngx-smart-components/tsconfig.lib.json"]` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets so `documentation.json` lands beside `.storybook/`.
3. In `preview.ts`, export `const preview: Preview = { tags: ['autodocs'] };` for global Docs tab.
4. Add `readonly label = input<string>('');` and `readonly selected = output<string>();` with `/** description */` JSDoc directly above each.
5. Add `.storybook/` to `compodocArgs` include path via `tsconfig.lib.json`; verify it includes `src/**/*.ts`.

**Correction from executor verification:** The advisor's point 1 is partially inaccurate -- the executor does NOT automatically inject `__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__`. The executor runs compodoc to generate `documentation.json`, but `preview.ts` must manually import the JSON and assign it to `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` using `@storybook/global`. This is confirmed by the webpack build cache showing the prior working `preview.ts`. The `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` import path does not exist in Storybook 10.3.5; the global write is the correct approach.
--- End Prior Strategic Direction ---

## Relevant File Contents

`packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` (storybook and build-storybook targets):
```json
"storybook": {
  "continuous": true,
  "executor": "@storybook/angular:start-storybook",
  "options": {
    "port": 4200,
    "configDir": "packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook",
    "browserTarget": "ngx-smart-components:build-storybook",
    "compodoc": false
  }
},
"build-storybook": {
  "executor": "@storybook/angular:build-storybook",
  "outputs": ["{options.outputDir}"],
  "options": {
    "outputDir": "dist/storybook/ngx-smart-components",
    "configDir": "packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook",
    "browserTarget": "ngx-smart-components:build-storybook",
    "compodoc": false
  }
}
```

`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`:
```json
{
  "extends": "../tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "emitDecoratorMetadata": true
  },
  "exclude": ["../**/*.spec.ts"],
  "include": [
    "../src/**/*.stories.ts",
    "../src/**/*.stories.js",
    "../src/**/*.stories.jsx",
    "../src/**/*.stories.tsx",
    "../src/**/*.stories.mdx",
    "*.js",
    "*.ts"
  ]
}
```

`packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.ts` (current):
```ts
import {
  ChangeDetectionStrategy,
  Component,
  ViewEncapsulation,
} from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'smart-ngx-smart-components',
  imports: [],
  template: `<p>NgxSmartComponents works!</p>`,
  styles: `
    :host {
      display: block;
    }
  `,
  encapsulation: ViewEncapsulation.Emulated,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
})
export class NgxSmartComponents {}
```

`packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts` (current):
```ts
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/angular';
import { NgxSmartComponents } from './ngx-smart-components';
import { expect } from 'storybook/test';

const meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {
  component: NgxSmartComponents,
  title: 'NgxSmartComponents',
};
export default meta;

type Story = StoryObj<NgxSmartComponents>;

export const Primary: Story = {
  args: {},
};

export const Heading: Story = {
  args: {},
  play: async ({ canvas }) => {
    await expect(canvas.getByText(/NgxSmartComponents works!/gi)).toBeTruthy();
  },
};
```

## Question

Given the executor correction that `__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` must be set manually in preview.ts, confirm: (a) is the plan's 7-step sequence correct as written, (b) does the `Heading` story's play assertion need updating when the template changes to `{{ label() }} works!` with default label `'NgxSmartComponents'`, and (c) should `@compodoc/compodoc` and `@storybook/global` be added as direct devDependencies in package.json even though both are already transitive deps?

